commit.message:
chore(license): remove Jolla Ltd. as a copyright holder

Apparently Jolla Ltd. did not provide any code changes while commit 46b8335
introduced a line like 'SPDX-FileCopyrightText: 2023 Jolla Ltd.' to almost
every file under src/.

build: correct some targets and their rules to prevent unneeded rebuilds

Without this patch the binaries are linked anew and the manpage gets
recreated with every 'make' and 'make install' call, even if no changes
to the sources have happened.

fix: check for return value of asprintf

in case of failure, free buffer and log error

Signed-off-by: Ulrich Weber <ulrich.weber@gmail.com>

fix: check for return value of chdir and system

compiler throws warn_unused_result warnings otherwise

Signed-off-by: Ulrich Weber <ulrich.weber@gmail.com>

fix: ike phase1 rekeying

Commit 074e1cebd5468bacaff36a5d94eb2bfcab30cc80 missed the
changes to use the provied i_cookie and r_cookie. See:
https://lists.unix-ag.uni-kl.de/pipermail/vpnc-devel/2015-June/004163.html

Signed-off-by: Ulrich Weber <ulrich.weber@gmail.com>

fix(openssl): dont use deprecated functions

EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA, RSA_size and RSA_public_decrypt got
deprecated in openssl 3.0, switch to EVP_PKEY_verify_recover

Code change mimics strongswan implementation from:
src/libstrongswan/plugins/openssl/openssl_rsa_public_key.c

Also works with openssl 1.1.1n from debian buster

Signed-off-by: Ulrich Weber <ulrich.weber@gmail.com>

style: rename pakets to packets

found by new codespell version

Signed-off-by: Ulrich Weber <ulrich.weber@gmail.com>

commit.message: Fix typos found by codespell

chore(license): Replace copyright and license text with SPDX identifiers

In case a one to one translation was possible I replaced the license
and copyright text with SPDX identifiers.
In case replacing wasn't possible completely I kept the part that goes
in detail to the copyright such as sections that explain the source of
the original code.

Resolves #39

Signed-off-by: Björn Bidar <bjorn.bidar@jolla.com>

chore(license): Add BSD-2-Clause license for BSD-2 licensed code

Only GPLv2 license was included before

Signed-off-by: Björn Bidar <bjorn.bidar@jolla.com>

chore(license): switch to GPLv2

Even though original project allowed forward compatibility (GPLv2+), moving back from GPLv3 to v2 for better abide to the original author's will, considered that there's no clear and strict need for GPLv3 in the first place.
Ref: #38

Even though original project allowed forward compatibility (GPLv2+), moving back from GPLv3 to v2 for better abide to the original author's will, considered that there's no clear and strict need for GPLv3 in the first place.
Ref: #38

commit.message: chore(config): update bugs report pointer (#37)

Fix typo in vpnc.c: encrytion -> encryption

found by Debian's lintian checker
Fix `-Wdangling-pointer`

Fix `-Wreserved-macro-identifier`

* https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Reserved-Names.html:
  "reserved names include [...] all identifiers regardless of use that begin with either two underscores [...]"

Add new option `--enable-weak-authentication`

* This is implemented similar to option `--enable-weak-encryption`.
* Weak authentication methods may also be enabled by putting
  `Enable weak authentication` into the configuration file.
* For the moment, MD5 is the only one considered to be weak.

Rename option `--enable-1des` to `--enable-weak-encryption`

* Adapt the parameter name accordingly to reflect this change.
* Deprecate old option `--enable-1des`.
* Add 3DES to the set of weak encryption methods.

Create the $(DOCDIR) in the install-doc rule

* When running with high -j, the install target would invoke `install-doc`
  before `install-common` actually created the $(DOCDIR), and then actually
  installing documentation would fail.

Fix `-Wimplicit-function-declaration`

* On Clang 15, this leads to hard failures:
    src/config.c:58:2: warning: call to undeclared function 'gettimeofday'; ISO C99 and later do not support implicit function declarations [-Wimplicit-function-declaration]
            gettimeofday(&tv, NULL);
            ^

https://bugs.gentoo.org/870727
https://discourse.llvm.org/t/configure-script-breakage-with-the-new-werror-implicit-function-declaration/65213
Fix `-Wunused-but-set-variable`
Fix `-Wheader-guard`
Allow to override $PREFIX and $DESTDIR from the command line
Make libgcrypt-config substitutable to allow passing an absolute path in
Do not query pkg-config for gnutls if compiling with OpenSSL's crypto

Replace deprecated index() by strchr()

The BSD legacy function index() was removed from POSIX standard in 2008,
and POSIX recommends its equivalent strchr() instead.
Some libc implementations for embedded systems do not have legacy functions
compiled in.
